  <title>
    <phrase>Flip Horizontally; Flip Vertically</phrase>
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  </title>

  <anchor id="gimp-image-flip-vertical"/>

  <indexterm significance="normal">
    <primary>Flip</primary>
  </indexterm>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

  <para>
    You can flip the image, or turn it over like a
    card, by using the <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Flip Horizontally</guimenuitem> or
    <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Flip Vertically</guimenuitem> commands.
    These commands work on the whole image. To flip a selection, use the
    <link linkend="gimp-tool-flip">Flip Tool</link>.
    To flip a layer, use the functions of the
    <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
      <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>L</accel>ayer</guimenu>
      <guisubmenu moreinfo="none"><accel>T</accel>ransform</guisubmenu>
    </menuchoice> menu or the
    <link linkend="gimp-tool-flip">Flip Tool</link>.
  </para>

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  


  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activate the Commands</phrase>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
    </title>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access the horizontal flip command from the image menubar
          through
          <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
            <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>I</accel>mage</guimenu>
            <guisubmenu moreinfo="none"><accel>T</accel>ransform</guisubmenu>
            <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Flip <accel>H</accel>orizontally</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access the vertical flip command from the image menubar
          through
          <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
            <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>I</accel>mage</guimenu>
            <guisubmenu moreinfo="none"><accel>T</accel>ransform</guisubmenu>
            <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Flip <accel>V</accel>ertically</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    

    

    

    

    

    

  </sect3>
